# Project Overview: QP Gen (Question Paper Generator)

This document provides a structured summary of the QP Gen project, suitable for inclusion in a PowerPoint presentation.

## 1. Project Architecture

The system follows a microservices-inspired architecture with a decoupled frontend and specialized backend services.

- **Frontend**: React.js (Vite)
  - Responsive Dashboard for Faculty and Admins.
  - Interactive Section Builder for question paper configuration.
  - Real-time preview and generation status.
- **Main Backend**: Node.js / Express
  - RESTful API gateway.
  - Authentication & Authorization (JWT-based).
  - Business logic for syllabus management and template configuration.
  - AI Integration: Powered by **Gemini Pro** for intelligent question generation.
- **PDF Service**: Java / Spring Boot
  - Specialized high-performance service for PDF rendering.
  - Handles complex layouts and mathematical notations.

---

## 2. Database Schema (MongoDB/Mongoose)

The project uses a NoSQL approach with MongoDB to handle semi-structured data like syllabus content and question templates.

### Key Entities & Models:

| Model | Description | Key Fields |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **User** | System users and roles. | email, role (admin/faculty), status, passwordHash |
| **Institution** | Organization context. | name, code, logoUrl, header/footer text |
| **Course** | Academic course details. | courseId, code, title, department, semester |
| **Syllabus** | Course curriculum data. | courseId, pdf (metadata/storage), extraction (text/chunks), units |
| **Template** | Question paper formats. | institutionId, format (JSON), type (internal/end_sem), status |
| **Note** | Supplementary materials. | courseId, unitNumber, extraction data (chunks) |
| **AuditLog** | System activity tracking. | userId, action, resourceType, details, timestamp |

### Relationships:
- **One-to-Many**: One Institution can have many Courses and Templates.
- **One-to-One**: Each Course has a specific Syllabus version.
- **Embedded Documents**: Syllabus and Notes contain embedded "chunks" of text for AI processing and embedding.

---

## 3. Core Features

- **AI-Powered Generation**: Automatically generates questions from syllabus content using Gemini Pro, adhering to Bloom's Taxonomy (BTL Levels K1-K6).
- **Template Management**: Define customizable question paper structures for different institutions and exam types (Internal/End Semester).
- **Syllabus Analysis**: Upload PDF syllabuses, extract text automatically, and break them down into units and topics.
- **Section Builder**: Granular control over sections, marks, and question distributions.
- **Secure Access**: Role-based access control (RBAC) ensuring only authorized faculty can generate papers.
- **PDF Generation**: Professional-grade PDF output with institutional branding and standardized formatting.

---

## 4. Tech Stack Summary

- **UI/UX**: React, Tailwind CSS, Lucide Icons.
- **Backend**: Node.js, Express, Mongoose.
- **PDF Engine**: Spring Boot, iText/OpenPDF (implied).
- **AI/ML**: Google Gemini Pro API, Ollama (local fallback).
- **Database**: MongoDB Atlas / Local MongoDB.
- **DevOps**: Maven (Java), NPM (JS).
